From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@example.com>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 15:20:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] luarocks: force stale tree locks during make

After earlier build failures or interrupted Bazel actions, LuaRocks can leave a
lock file under the generated `luarocks_tree` directory:

  luarocks_tree/lockfile.lfs

The following retry then fails with:

  command 'make' requires exclusive write access ... try --force-lock

Kong already makes `luarocks_make` depend on `luarocks_target` to avoid the
known concurrency issue between those two actions.  Use LuaRocks' own
`--force-lock` recovery switch for the make step so a stale lock from a
previous failed action does not block a clean retry.
---
 build/luarocks/templates/luarocks_make.sh | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/build/luarocks/templates/luarocks_make.sh b/build/luarocks/templates/luarocks_make.sh
index 96cbc9b..21864b6 100644
--- a/build/luarocks/templates/luarocks_make.sh
+++ b/build/luarocks/templates/luarocks_make.sh
@@ -15,7 +15,7 @@ mkdir -p $(dirname $@)
 # alias LDOC command to true(1) command
 export LDOC=true
 
-$luarocks_exec make --no-doc 2>&1 >$@.tmp
+$luarocks_exec make --no-doc --force-lock 2>&1 >$@.tmp
 
 # only generate the output when the command succeeds
-mv $@.tmp $@
\ No newline at end of file
+mv $@.tmp $@
-- 
